<paragraph id="E97036DD3F1AFF8DFF76FDE3FDF3FD9E" blockId="47.[151,1437,613,1216]" box="[151,531,613,640]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Size. Reaches 
<quantity id="2E379B383F1AFF8DFEDBFDE3FE66FD61" box="[314,390,613,640]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" unit="cm" value="8.2">8.2 cm</quantity>
total length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F1AFF8DFF26FD0FFB3DFB21" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F1AFF8DFF26FD0FFE0EFCB6" blockId="47.[151,1437,613,1216]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Morphology. D VI + I,10; A I,9; P 15. Body elongate, the depth 
<quantity id="2E379B383F1AFF8DFC4AFD0FFC0DFD42" box="[939,1005,649,676]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.651" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" unit="in" value="6.5">6.5 in</quantity>
standard length. Head subcylindrical, snout short and blunt. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F1AFF8DFE6DFD2BFC9AFD26" bold="true" box="[396,890,685,711]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Eyes elevated above dorsal profile of head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F1AFF8DFC69FD2BFC3BFD29" box="[904,987,685,712]" captionStart="FIGURE 46" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1029,1053]" captionTargetBox="[173,1414,181,1005]" captionTargetId="figure-19@40.[173,1414,181,1005]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 46. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Cryptocentrus steinhardti Goren &amp; Stern, 2021. Photo by P. Louisy, Kas, Turkey, Eastern Mediterranean." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601713" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601713/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). Caudal peduncle slender, clearly lower than body height. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F1AFF8DFE89FD57FBD8FD0A" bold="true" box="[360,1080,721,747]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Third and fourth spines of first dorsal fin longest, elongate</emphasis>
. Second dorsal fin subequal in height to first fin. Pelvic fins joined medially, reaching anus. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F1AFF8DFCD8FD73FA7DFCEE" bold="true" box="[825,1437,757,783]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Caudal fin rounded, clearly longer than head length</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F1AFF8DFF41FC9FFF13FCD5" box="[160,243,793,820]" captionStart="FIGURE 46" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1029,1053]" captionTargetBox="[173,1414,181,1005]" captionTargetId="figure-19@40.[173,1414,181,1005]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 46. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Cryptocentrus steinhardti Goren &amp; Stern, 2021. Photo by P. Louisy, Kas, Turkey, Eastern Mediterranean." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601713" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601713/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). Body covered with scales; no scales on head and pectoral-fin base, but scales not visible or poorly visible on live specimen photographs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F1AFF8DFF26FCE7FC28FC06" blockId="47.[151,1437,613,1216]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F1AFF8DFE60FCE7FB63FC9A" bold="true" box="[385,1155,865,891]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Body whitish or yellowish with three slightly oblique brown bars</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F1AFF8DFB72FCE7FB06FC9D" box="[1171,1254,865,892]" captionStart="FIGURE 46" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1029,1053]" captionTargetBox="[173,1414,181,1005]" captionTargetId="figure-19@40.[173,1414,181,1005]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 46. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Cryptocentrus steinhardti Goren &amp; Stern, 2021. Photo by P. Louisy, Kas, Turkey, Eastern Mediterranean." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601713" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601713/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
), the first below first dorsal fin, second and third below anterior and posterior part of second dorsal fin respectively, large irregular brown spot or bar at caudal-fin base, and scattered brown spots about pupil size in pale interspaces; predorsal area, nape and dorsal part of opercle with small irregular dark brown blotches.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F1AFF8DFF26FC77FD97FBED" blockId="47.[151,1437,613,1216]" box="[199,631,1009,1036]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F1AFF8DFE9EFC77FD90FBEA" authorityName="Alien" baseAuthorityName="Klunzinger" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[383,624,1009,1035]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Oxyurichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petersii">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F1AFF8DFE9EFC77FD90FBEA" box="[383,624,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Oxyurichthys petersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F1AFF8DFF26FB93FB41FBB5" blockId="47.[151,1437,613,1216]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Habitat. In the Mediterranean, inhabits soft substrata of open sand areas at depths of 
<quantity id="2E379B383F1AFF8DFB8DFB93FB30FBD1" box="[1132,1232,1045,1072]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.55" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" unit="m" value="45.5" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="11.0">11–80 m</quantity>
; observed to share a burrow with snapping shrimps (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F1AFF8DFDEEFBBFFD17FBB2" author="Goren, M. &amp; Stern, N." box="[527,759,1081,1107]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="12136" refId="ref55567" refString="Goren, M. &amp; Stern, N. (2021) Cryptocentrus steinhardti (Actynopterygii: Gobiidae): a new species of shrimp-goby, a new invasive to the Mediterranean Sea. PeerJ, 9, e 12136. https: // doi. org / 10.7717 / peerj. 12136" type="journal article" year="2021">Goren &amp; Stern 2021</bibRefCitation>
; P. Louisy unpublished observations).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F1AFF8DFF26FBDBFB3DFB21" blockId="47.[151,1437,613,1216]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<materialsCitation id="59A73C803F1AFF8DFF26FBDBFB39FB21" collectorName="Bogorodsky &amp; Goren" country="Turkey" location="eastern Mediterranean" municipality="southern Israeli" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" specimenCount="1">
Geographic distribution. At present is known only from 
<specimenCount id="FFC9FD543F1AFF8DFCD3FBDBFC05FB96" box="[818,997,1117,1143]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
caught in the 
<location id="EC1060063F1AFF8DFB9FFBD8FA96FB96" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:616687CB3F1AFF8DFF76FE5DFB3DFB21:EC1060063F1AFF8DFB9FFBD8FA96FB96" box="[1150,1398,1117,1144]" country="Turkey" municipality="southern Israeli" name="eastern Mediterranean" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">eastern Mediterranean</location>
off the 
<collectingMunicipality id="0914ACA73F1AFF8DFF5EFB07FE8BFB7A" box="[191,363,1153,1179]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">southern Israeli</collectingMunicipality>
coast and underwater photographs taken in southern 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F1AFF8DFC54FB07FBE5FB7A" box="[949,1029,1153,1179]" name="Turkey" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Turkey</collectingCountry>
at Kas (
